rComments: Tbh he wasn't the best prof when it came to lectures, I felt confused alot, but he's incredibly helpful and makes sure you understand when it comes time to office hours and such. He gives people chances and that's probably the best thing.
Really really liked him! Good prof, helpful and really nice! Didn't love the class, but didn't hate it either because of him

He won't be back again for next year but he was a good teacher. Tests were so easy since you were always able to predict the short answer question. Got an 84 in his class, with barely any studying so.
He is the best economics professor. He is very caring and patient. I like the economy again because of him. Hope he is backing one year after and teach eco 300 level course.

Professor Mahone is an absolute gem. He cares about his students and he makes this course do-able and not unnecessarily hard. His tests are fair and he looks for ways so students get their marks up. He opens up missed homework and quizzes in our favour. Its his last year at UTM and he will be greatly missed. MAC is lucky to have him he's amazing!
He's the best!!! Probably one of the most caring and helpful people!!!

I can see why people enjoyed his teaching style but it just didn't work on me. The lectures were okay I guess but not the best for everyone. Really clear he cares though and will help with anything you need.

Professor Mahone is definitely one of the best professors at UTM who can present material in the way so we all can understand. He is very supportive, answers any questions. On tests he always asks what we have covered, no suprises. If you attend lectures, tutorials and make online h/w you will be fine.

Am amazing professor, hands down my favourite one at utm. He's super approachable outside class and makes sure you understand your concepts. if you don't, he may even take up an hour during his office hours to explain! he's very caring and understanding too - would definitely recommend
BEST PROF EVER. I LOVE HIM.

I am a student who register with accessibility. He makes me felt that it is okay to be different. He posted mark really quick even he received the test late. (other prof gives me 0 first and post the mark one week later) He even encourages student to be a volunteer note taker both in his mails and lecture. He is caring about student a lot!

The best professor in economic's course. He is patient and caring for students. I took eco100 and eco202 with him. Go to office hour to ask question! Sometimes he will spend one hour to answer your questions.
the best Prof in utm!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! extremely caring and is a great professor!

He would want his students to pass and actually give them so much part marks rather than losing all the marks bc of a small mistake. He's very approachable during his office hours. I hated eco100 but every time I go to his office hours, I get everything.

Mahone was an awesome prof. had him the first year he taught at utm and he did a good job. No surprises on tests. Extremely caring and wanted you to understand the material instead of just memorize. would def take him again

Mahone is one of the best profs in UTM. He explains his concepts very well and if you do the readings, attend the lectures, and do all the homework assigned you will get a good grade. There are no surprises when it comes to the tests. He is also extremely helpful in office hours.

Thoroughly enjoyed taking Eco 100 with Mahone. He is very clear and only tests you on what he covers in class so it is very important to go to lectures and take notes. He is very helpful in his office hours and is very nice to all students.

rComments: Professor Mahone is fabulous, there are no surprises if you've read your stuff and attended his lectures. There are weekly online quizzes which can get slightly annoying. But they're also worth 20% of your grade so it's a great booster. Pay close attention to lecture concepts as you will be tested on them.
Very passionate about the course and teaching the material thoroughly to students. Is easily approachable and gave a fair exam!

I love this prof!! he is one of the best professors at UTM. Although ECO100 was challenging, I very much enjoyed his lectures. Very respectful, and gives second chances for grade improvement. Would highly recommend taking his classes!!
Amazing prof and explains concepts thoroughly! Always willing to answer questions and the feedback you'll get really helps.
Awesome professor. Wants you to learn and succeed. His tests are a little bit tricky. If you go to his office hours he will explain concepts more thoroughly. His lectures are clear and concise.

He is a really helpful prof! Took ECO100 with him. First couple tests were tricky but afterwards you will start understanding them much better. Make sure you make the best use of his office hours and watch out for those online quizzes.. they are worth 20% of the total mark and if you put time and energy into them, marks are up for grabs! Cheers!
Really wants students to understand and learn. Very passionate about economics studies; overall great guy!
